{
  "_comment": "Worked example — feedback-memo memo subtype. Calibrated from the studio raytheon-pitch-strategy canary (2026-06-02): a studio-side feedback memo TO a CEO on his draft roadmap thesis (~5K words). The memo engages another document directly, validates parts, recommends sharpening, and proposes a concrete pitch backbone. There is no 'the company,' no ask, no founder section — the recommendation target is positional (sharpen the thesis, adopt the pitch backbone), not financial. For this shape, forceful brevity beats comprehensive defensibility — every other rubric dim rewards additions, so the calibration prose tells the reviewer to score on positional clarity rather than investment-memo coverage. To use: copy this file to <thread>/.anvil.json, drop the _comment lines, and tune the calibration prose / target range to your thread. See anvil/skills/memo/SKILL.md §'Rubric overrides and non-investment-memo shapes' for the full contract.",

  "max_iterations": 6,
  "target_length": { "words": [4000, 6000] },

  "rubric_overrides": {
    "memo_subtype": "feedback-memo",

    "dim_1_calibration": "feedback-to-third-party — score on position clarity (does the memo take a clear position on the engaged document and propose a concrete next move?), not on single ranked investment recommendation. This memo has no 'the company' and no check-size ask; the recommendation target is positional, not financial. Do not score down dim 1 for 'no invest/pass/conditional recommendation' — score dim 1 on whether the positional recommendation (validate / sharpen / replace / extend) is unambiguous and whether the proposed pitch backbone (or equivalent next-move artifact) is concrete.",

    "dim_4_calibration": "feedback-memo — score dim 4 on whether the memo names the risks of the position it is recommending the third party adopt, not on whether it names the operating risks of a portfolio company. The relevant risk surface is positional (where could the proposed sharpening / pitch backbone fail to land?), not operational.",

    "dim_5_calibration": "secondary for feedback-memo shape — score dim 5 on whether market framing supports the positional recommendation, not on whether the memo does original TAM/SAM/SOM sizing. Feedback memos engage a third party's existing positioning; the load-bearing question is whether the proposed sharpening matches the market the third party is actually in, not whether the memo independently sizes that market.",

    "dim_6_calibration": "secondary for feedback-memo shape — score dim 6 on whether the financial framing supports the positional recommendation, not on whether the memo does original unit-economics or scenario modeling. Feedback memos do not carry an investment ask; financial reasoning enters only insofar as it pressure-tests the positional recommendation.",

    "dim_7_calibration": "target length 4000-6000 words; score against declared target. Forceful brevity is load-bearing for this shape — every other rubric dim rewards additions, so the dim 7 anchor must hold the line on the declared range. A feedback memo that drifts long has typically over-defended a position the operator wanted stated forcefully and moved on from.",

    "target_length": { "words": [4000, 6000] }
  }
}
